Now I have the complete picture. Here's my analysis of the error and the relevant code sections.

---

## Root Cause Analysis

The error `'ClaudeContentBlockToolResult' object has no attribute 'id'` is an HTTP 500 from the Anthropic API. It means the API received a `tool_result` content block and tried to access `.id` on it, but `tool_result` blocks don't have an `id` field -- they have `tool_use_id`. The error is triggered server-side by Anthropic when the request payload is malformed.

The bug is in the Anthropic provider's `convertMessages` function at `/c/Users/Administrator/clawdbot/node_modules/.ignored/@mariozechner/pi-ai/dist/providers/anthropic.js`, specifically lines **515-528** where `cache_control` is added to the last user message's last content block.

## The Exact Bug

`/c/Users/Administrator/clawdbot/node_modules/.ignored/@mariozechner/pi-ai/dist/providers/anthropic.js`, lines 484-528:

```javascript
// Lines 484-513: toolResult messages are grouped into a single "user" message
// with content blocks of type "tool_result"
else if (msg.role === "toolResult") {
    const toolResults = [];
    toolResults.push({
        type: "tool_result",
        tool_use_id: msg.toolCallId,
        content: convertContentBlocks(msg.content),
        is_error: msg.isError,
    });
    // ... look ahead for consecutive toolResults ...
    params.push({
        role: "user",
        content: toolResults,  // <-- array of { type: "tool_result", tool_use_id, ... }
    });
}

// Lines 515-528: cache_control is added to the LAST content block of the last user message
if (params.length > 0) {
    const lastMessage = params[params.length - 1];
    if (lastMessage.role === "user") {
        if (Array.isArray(lastMessage.content)) {
            const lastBlock = lastMessage.content[lastMessage.content.length - 1];
            if (lastBlock &&
                (lastBlock.type === "text" || lastBlock.type === "image" || lastBlock.type === "tool_result")) {
                lastBlock.cache_control = { type: "ephemeral" };  // <-- THIS IS THE PROBLEM
            }
        }
    }
}
```

When the last user message contains `tool_result` blocks, `cache_control: { type: "ephemeral" }` is added to the last `tool_result` block. The Anthropic API then processes this block and apparently tries to access `.id` on the `ClaudeContentBlockToolResult` object (their internal representation), which doesn't exist because `tool_result` blocks use `tool_use_id`, not `id`. The `cache_control` annotation on a `tool_result` block is either unsupported or triggers a server-side bug.

## All Relevant Code Sections

### 1. Where tool_result blocks are constructed for the API

`/c/Users/Administrator/clawdbot/node_modules/.ignored/@mariozechner/pi-ai/dist/providers/anthropic.js`, lines 484-513:
```javascript
