## The Fix

The fix is in `/c/Users/Administrator/clawdbot/node_modules/.ignored/@mariozechner/pi-ai/dist/providers/anthropic.js`, line 523. Remove `"tool_result"` from the type check so `cache_control` is never added to `tool_result` blocks:

```javascript
// BEFORE (line 523):
if (lastBlock && (lastBlock.type === "text" || lastBlock.type === "image" || lastBlock.type === "tool_result")) {

// AFTER:
if (lastBlock && (lastBlock.type === "text" || lastBlock.type === "image")) {
```

This happens when the conversation's last message to the API is a user message containing only `tool_result` blocks (i.e., the agent just executed tools and is about to get the next assistant response). Adding `cache_control` to a `tool_result` block causes Anthropic's server to crash with the `'ClaudeContentBlockToolResult' object has no attribute 'id'` error.

The error is intermittent because it only triggers when the last user message in the payload happens to be a tool-result-only message (no text/image blocks), which depends on conversation flow.
